-- Mercator 2011 Net Income Falls 22% to 23.5 Million Euros
-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 2012-02-27T15:46:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-27/mercator-2011-net-income-falls-22-to-23-5-million-euros-1-.html
Mercator Poslovni Sistem (MELR)  d.d., the
largest retail store chain in the Balkans, said net income fell
22 percent last year to 23.5 million euros.  Revenue advanced 5.3 percent to 2.93 million euros. The
biggest gain was recorded in  Serbia , where the Slovenian company
increased sales 17.6 percent from a year earlier, the Ljubljana-
based company said in an e-mailed statement today.  The company proposed a dividend of 4.50 euros on 2011
earnings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  